    "justification": "Three conjuncts license the conclusion: (1) ΔAUROC > 0.02 passes the pre-registered STRONG threshold for biophysics adding information beyond age+length+class; (2) absolute M1 AUROC > 0.7 ensures the model is substantively predictive (not just incrementally improved on a noise floor); (3) n > 5,000 in the age-matched band ensures the 5-fold CV variance is bounded.",
    "failure_mode": "If s_delta_auroc fell below 0.02 OR s_auroc_m1 fell below 0.7, the within-age claim would be revoked. The H3K9me3 negative-control prediction (separate claim) would also need to hold for this to read as evidence of selective biophysical recruitment to bivalent chromatin rather than generic 'biophysics predicts everything.'"
  },
